de.tub.processor.staypoint
Class GeoStayPointProcessor

java.lang.Object
  de.tub.processor.staypoint.GeoStayPointProcessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Observer, IProcessor<User>, ISimulator<Integer>
public class GeoStayPointProcessor
extends Object
implements IProcessor<User>, ISimulator<Integer>, Observer

This processor takes user entities and assesses, based on the geographic points of the each user, their stay points.

As this processor implements the ISimulator interface it can be used in simulation mode in which the stay points of each user are summed up and can be accessed after the processing of every user. The computed stay points are not persisted while in simulation mode.

Author:
Sebastian Oelke

Constructor Detail

GeoStayPointProcessor

public GeoStayPointProcessor(int distanceThreshold,
                             int timeThreshold)
With this constructor the distance threshold as well as the time threshold has to be defined. The simulation mode is turned off by default.

Parameters:
distanceThreshold - the maximum distance two locations/points of a user can be apart and still be detected as a stay point.
timeThreshold - the time a user has to stay within a certain area to be identified as a stay point.
